==English==
===Noun===
'''faeces''' (''plural'')

# [[animal]] [[digested]] [[food]] or [[waste]] [[discharge]]d from the [[bowel]]s, typically into a toilet.

====Usage====
Used primarily in British and South African English. 

====Alternative spellings====
*'''fæces''' (''dated'')
*'''feces''' (''US'') 

====Synonyms====
*[[excrement]]
*(''of birds only''): [[guano]]
*[[manure]] (''not used of human faeces'')
*(''[[euphemistic]] or [[hypocoristic]]''): [[doo]], [[poo]], and [[poop]]
*(''vulgar''; ''all [[uncountable]] except as indicated''): [[crap]], [[shit]], [[turd]] (''singular, [[countable]]'')

